The paper proposes a new family of variational approximations that can be applied to a wide range of graphical models, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on improving the lower bound on the marginal likelihood of the data and the use of nonparametric kernel density estimation suggest that the paper is most likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies the method to hierarchical logistic regression and nonlinear matrix factorization models, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) and statistical methods (cs.ST) in the derivation of the nonparametric approximation.
